content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide a solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure has 2 layers
- Bottom layer consists of:
  * A red arch piece in the center
  * Two orange triangular ramps on either side of the arch
- Top layer consists of:
  * A green rectangular block
  * An orange triangular piece on top

Total blocks needed: 5 pieces

Looking at the Block Dictionary:
- For the arch: Block #1 (red arch piece)
- For the side ramps: Block #14 and Block #15 (orange ramp pieces)
- For the green top: Block #7 (green rectangular block)
- For the top triangle: Block #11 (orange triangular piece)

Assembly Order (from bottom to top, left to right):
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1
    Step2: Move block with index 14
    Step3: Move block with index 15
    Step4: Move block with index 7
    Step5: Move block with index 11
}

This assembly order will build the structure from the ground up, starting with the arch, adding the side ramps, placing the green rectangular block on top, and finally adding the orange triangular piece at the very top.
